        " from the camp at Ardea. They found Lucretia in her room. She explained what had happened and after exacting an oath of vengeance— Pledge me your solemn word that the adulterer shall not go unpunished. — T.L. I.58. and while they were discussing the matter, drew the poignard and stabbed herself in her heart.     In another version Collatinus and Brutus were encountered returning to Rome unaware, were briefed, and were brought to the death scene. Brutus happened to be a politically motivated participant. By kinship he was a Tarquin on his mothers side, the son of Tarquinia, daughter of ": null
